parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the PODS can cause the passenger airbag to be disabled, increasing the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The passenger airbag off warning light remains illuminated with an occupant seated in the passenger's side seat
the safety system malfunction warning appears
the airbag dash light is illuminated
the airbags and other safety systems do not work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to a failure to deploy in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality to occupants. Additionally, the constant warning lights and messages can cause driver distraction and anxiety.
symptoms: frequent "Safety system: malfunction! See owner's manual" and "Audi pre sense: currently restricted. See owner's manual" messages on the dashboard

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel system leak or fuel spit back can cause a fire or explosion, potentially leading to loss of life, property damage, and adjacent home damage.
symptoms: refueling shutoff at any rate of fuel delivery
strong fuel odor in the garage or surrounding area
persistent fuel odor for an extended period.
